== {{project name long}} Linux Installer ==
What does the {{project name long}} Linux Installer do?

The previous only available method for using {{project name long}} for VirtualBox was to follow the instructions on the [[VirtualBox|{{project name long}} for VirtualBox]] wiki page. {{project name long}} Linux Installer simplifies the process of downloading {{project name long}}, installing VirtualBox and importing {{project name long}} into VirtualBox. In more details:

# Check from the script name. Valid names are <code>installer-dist</code>, <code>{{project_name_short_lowercase}}-installer-cli</code> and <code>{{project_name_short_lowercase}}-installer-xfce</code>.
# Parse command line options.
# Check if system has enough disk space, enough RAM memory, virtualization support and advice the user if any system requirements are not satisfied.
# Install necessary packages for the script to run using APT package manager such as <code>signify</code>, <code>curl</code>, <code>rsync</code>, <code>vboxmanage</code> (if using VirtualBox).
# Enable fasttrack repository if not enabled yet and only if using Debian since it is required to install VirtualBox.
# Query {{project name long}} version number using [[API]] if no version specified as a command line option.
# If the Virtual Machine(s) were previously imported, ask the user to boot the virtual system(s).
# If the Virtual Machine(s) files were previously downloaded, do authenticity and integrity checks.
# If this is the first run, download necessary files, do authenticity and integrity check, import system(s) and try to start Virtual Machine(s).

Other features:

* Download resumption support thanks to internal use of rsync.
* Simple integrity check thanks to internal use of rsync.
* <code>--onion</code> support.
* Default download folder: <code>~/installer-dist-download</code>
* Retain a log of all executed commands in the download folder and along with that a copy of the script which has been executed at that time.
* [https://github.com/Kicksecure/usability-misc/blob/master/man/installer-dist.1.ronn <code>installer-dist</code> man page]

